## [Topics](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#topics)

### [Instance Properties](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#Instance-Properties)

[`var endIndex: ClosedRange<Bound>.Index`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/endindex)The range’s “past the end” position—that is, the position one greater than the last valid subscript argument.[`var isEmpty: Bool`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/isempty)A Boolean value indicating whether the range contains no elements.[`var startIndex: ClosedRange<Bound>.Index`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/startindex)The position of the first element in the range.### [Instance Methods](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#Instance-Methods)

[`func distance(from: ClosedRange<Bound>.Index, to: ClosedRange<Bound>.Index) -> Int`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/distance(from:to:))Returns the distance between two indices.[`func index(ClosedRange<Bound>.Index, offsetBy: Int) -> ClosedRange<Bound>.Index`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index(_:offsetby:))Returns an index that is the specified distance from the given index.[`func index(after: ClosedRange<Bound>.Index) -> ClosedRange<Bound>.Index`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index(after:))Returns the position immediately after the given index.### [Subscripts](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#Subscripts)

[`subscript(ClosedRange<Bound>.Index) -> Bound`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/subscript(_:)-60m0l)Accesses the element at specified position.[`subscript(Range<ClosedRange<Bound>.Index>) -> Slice<ClosedRange<Bound>>`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/subscript(_:)-vph6)Accesses a contiguous subrange of the collection’s elements.### [Type Aliases](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#Type-Aliases)

[`typealias Indices`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/indices)A type that represents the indices that are valid for subscripting the collection, in ascending order.[`typealias SubSequence`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/subsequence)A collection representing a contiguous subrange of this collection’s elements. The subsequence shares indices with the original collection.### [Enumerations](/documentation/swift/closedrange/collection-implementations#Enumerations)

[`enum Index`](/documentation/swift/closedrange/index)A type that represents a position in the collection.
